    </mj-section> 
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Historic trial</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-11-1.jpg" alt="Historic trial" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu took the stand in his corruption <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20241210-israel-s-netanyahu-prepares-to-take-the-stand-in-historic-corruption-trial" target="_blank">trial</a>, which makes him the first sitting Israeli leader to testify as a criminal defendant. His charges include bribery, fraud, breach of trust, and being accused of trading regulatory favors for positive media coverage and accepting expensive gifts. He denies wrongdoing, calling the case a politically driven “witch hunt” against his policies.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The trial is held at a time when Netanyahu is navigating Israel’s war in <a href="https://www.history.com/news/gaza-conflict-history-israel-palestine" target="_blank">Gaza</a> and growing regional <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/10/02/middleeast/israel-lebanon-regional-war-analysis-intl/index.html" target="_blank">tensions</a>. The protestors against Netanyahu demanded his resignation, and his former political allies refused to serve in government, while the supporters viewed the charges as the justice system's bias and overreach. Netanyahu rejected the proposal to step down and strongly criticized law enforcement, media, and the court. The testimony will occur six hours a day, three days a week, for several weeks.​</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">China maritime movements</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-11-2.jpg" alt="China maritime movements" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4; filter: blur(5px)">Tensions between China and Taiwan have <a href="https://www.dw.com/en/taiwan-says-china-deploying-largest-naval-fleet-in-decades/a-71008022" target="_blank">escalated</a> significantly, as Taiwan’s Defense Ministry reported the largest Chinese naval deployment near the island in nearly three decades. Over the past 24 hours, 47 Chinese military aircraft and 12 warships were detected, marking the highest military presence in months. The deployment is even more significant than the <a href="https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/politics/article/3187774/beijings-war-games-taiwan-after-pelosis-trip-spark-concerns" target="_blank">2022 war games</a> triggered by former U.S. House Speaker Nancy Pelosi’s visit. Taiwanese forces are on high alert. Defense Ministry officials described the Chinese navy as forming “two walls” in the Pacific, signaling an effort to frame the Taiwan Strait as China’s internal waters.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4; filter: blur(5px)">Relations have worsened following Taiwanese President Lai Ching-te’s <a href="https://apnews.com/article/taiwan-us-china-lai-ching-te-hawaii-guam-7abcd0e5803fdb7f20615fd394aca91b" target="_blank">U.S. visit</a>, which Beijing condemned. China views Taiwan as part of its territory, while Taiwan asserts its sovereignty and relies on U.S. support for defense. Since Lai Ching-te took office, China has launched two large-scale military drills around Taiwan. ​</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->

    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
